        <p>While medical jurisprudence textbooks such as <xref ref-type="bibr" rid="b56">Taylor</xref>, <italic>Medical jurisprudence</italic> (p. 298), had long argued otherwise, it was still considered in some quarters that when the lungs sank in water, this suggested that the child had never breathed and had thus been born dead.</p>
