        <label>29</label>
        <p>That is, the child had to have reached a stage in its development that made a living birth possible, taken at this time to be completion of the seventh month of intra-uterine life, and to have been fully born. Destruction of the child <italic>during</italic> the parturient process&#x2014;that is, as the child was in the process of being born&#x2014;did not constitute an offence against the law.</p>
