        <p>Private members' bills in 1908 and 1914 had attempted to make stillbirths registrable but were both squashed by the government on the grounds &#x2018;that they would involve considerable public expenditure or were badly drafted or contained objectionable incidental matter&#x2019;. See <xref ref-type="bibr" rid="b50">Rose</xref>, <italic>Massacre of the innocents</italic>, p. 133.</p>
